Description: Fix compatibility with bison 3.8.2
 bison 3.8.2 (Debian Bookworm) removed support for the YYPARSE_PARAM
 and YYLEX_PARAM preprocessor macros and the %pure-parser directive.
 Replace them with the modern %define api.pure full, %parse-param and
 %lex-param directives. Update the _mdir_error macro signature to match
 the new two-argument form required by bison 3.x pure parsers.
 Update the _mdir_parse() forward declaration in parse.c to use void *
 instead of mdir_line *** to match the signature generated by bison.
Origin: vendor
Forwarded: not-needed
Author: Gustavo Perez Reyes <ghreyes71@gmail.com>
Last-Update: 2026-03-03

Index: b/dirsynt.y
===================================================================
